# legacy path - do not remove. Sub-Iterate F of agent_docs migration (2026-04-28).
/agent_docs/
# Canonical designs home is .shipwright/designs/.
# Anchored to root since 2026-05-02 self-adoption to allow .shipwright/designs/.
# See docs/migrations/.shipwright-designs-relocation.md.
# legacy path - do not remove. Sub-Iterate F of designs migration (2026-04-27).
/designs/
# Canonical planning home is .shipwright/planning/.
# Kept as a safety net against re-tracked legacy files.
# Anchored to root since 2026-05-02 self-adoption to allow .shipwright/planning/.
# See docs/migrations/.shipwright-relocation.md.
# legacy path - do not remove. Sub-Iterate F (2026-04-27).
/planning/
# Canonical tool-call counter is .shipwright/toolcall_count.
# legacy path - do not remove. Renamed 2026-04-29 (drive-by, no migration).
.shipwright_toolcall_count
# Canonical compliance home is .shipwright/compliance/.
# Anchored to root since 2026-05-02 self-adoption to allow .shipwright/compliance/.
# See docs/migrations/.shipwright-compliance-relocation.md.
# legacy path - do not remove. Sub-Iterate F of compliance migration (2026-04-29).
/compliance/

# Per-tree triage outbox buffer (campaign 2026-06-08-triage-outbox-delivery, D1).
# .shipwright/triage.outbox.jsonl is a GITIGNORED transient buffer for idle-main
# background producers; the D2 sweep folds it into the iterate PR branch + GCs it.
# It is ALREADY ignored by the `/.shipwright/*` wildcard in the managed block
# below — and is deliberately NOT given a `!` re-include there (only the tracked
# `triage.jsonl` is). This comment is documentation only (no rule), so it stays
# OUTSIDE the managed/congruence-checked block. D3 propagates the same intent to
# adopted repos via the canon template.

