.worktrees/

# Local VS Code multi-root workspace (not part of the public repo)
.shipwright-webui/

# === .shipwright/ artefact whitelist (public-launch hardening) ===
# Shipwright self-adoption (2026-05-02): the framework adopts itself, so the
# canonical .shipwright/ SDLC-doc homes are tracked. Whitelist approach:
# ignore everything under .shipwright/, then re-include only the canonical
# homes — robust against future transient runtime files (locks, loop state,
# runs, security reports, triage logs) that should never be committed.
#
# The rule-lines between the BEGIN/END markers below are kept congruent with
# shared/templates/shipwright-gitignore.template (the SSoT propagated to every
# consuming project). Drift is caught by
# shared/tests/test_gitignore_template_congruent.py — a future ADR adding a
# gitignored .shipwright/ dir must edit the template AND this block.
# === BEGIN Shipwright canonical .shipwright artifact-ignore (managed) ===
/.shipwright/*
!/.shipwright/adopt/
!/.shipwright/agent_docs/
!/.shipwright/compliance/
!/.shipwright/designs/
!/.shipwright/planning/
# triage.jsonl is the tracked SSoT backlog (mirrors shipwright_events.jsonl); the
# .lock + .bak stay ignored by the /.shipwright/* wildcard above (negation is exact).
!/.shipwright/triage.jsonl
# triage.outbox.jsonl is the per-tree, GITIGNORED background-triage buffer
# (campaign 2026-06-08-triage-outbox-delivery): idle-main producers append HERE
# (never the tracked triage.jsonl), and setup_iterate_worktree sweeps it into the
# iterate PR branch. It MUST stay ignored — the explicit line below is redundant
# with the /.shipwright/* wildcard but pins the intent so a future `!`-negation
# can never silently start tracking the buffer. DO NOT add a `!`-re-include for it.
/.shipwright/triage.outbox.jsonl
# Re-exclude transient / internal / generated content inside the doc homes:
/.shipwright/adopt/backups/
/.shipwright/adopt/screenshots/
/.shipwright/agent_docs/decision-drops/
/.shipwright/agent_docs/visual/
# Stop-hook live state (session_handoff.md, build_dashboard.md,
# triage_inbox.md) — written every Stop event in every plugin; tracked
# variants are produced only by iterate-finalize as the single producer.
# See iterate-2026-05-27-tracked-artifacts-single-producer-and-finalize-sandbox.
/.shipwright/agent_docs/runtime/
/.shipwright/compliance/skill-compliance/
# Defensive (non-anchored): a stray nested `.shipwright/locks/` (e.g. a bloat
# marker written by a hook whose cwd != repo-root) must never leak. The
# root-anchored `/.shipwright/*` above misses nested copies. The real fix is the
# main_repo_root resolver in check_file_size + bloat_gate_on_stop
# (iterate-2026-06-09); this is belt-and-suspenders.
**/.shipwright/locks/
# === END Shipwright canonical .shipwright artifact-ignore (managed) ===
